Coster et al. v. Fiske. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. June 6, 1890.) Action by Charles Coster and another against Oliver Fiske. The receiver appointed in supplementary proceedings appeals from an order denying his motion to compel the transfer of two policies of life insurance.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

J. Eustice for appellant. G. Bliss, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The order appealed from should be affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
